Source: <nobr><font color="#ff0000">The name "%1" is already in use.</font></nobr>
en-us: <nobr><font color="#ff0000">The name "%1" is already in use.</font></nobr>

Context: Error message that is displayed if the user tries to set the name of a new custom emulation device to one that already exists.
Source: The name "%1" is already in use.
en-us: The name "%1" is already in use.

Context: Error message that is displayed if the user tries to set the name of a new custom emulation device to one that is used internally, and unavailable for the user. The name is reserved by the system.
